        (30161, 'Donnie Dunagan', '1934-08-16', 'From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia.

Donald "Donnie" Roan Dunagan  (born August 16, 1934) is a semi-retired American former child actor and United States Marine Corps drill instructor. He was a voice actor in the Bambi film, providing the voice of Young Bambi. A 28-page interview, his first after decades as a "lost Hollywood player," can be found in the book "Earth vs. the Sci-Fi Filmmakers" (Jefferson NC: McFarland &amp; Co., 2006) by Tom Weaver.

Description above from the Wikipedia article Donnie Dunagan, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia', 'San Antonio, Texas, USA', 2, '/9zZfLYr9kOsK8X8D5AT2Uc5ADHg.jpg'),
