Monet Happy Mazur (born April 17, 1976) is an American actress, model and musician.', 'Los Angeles, California, USA', 1, '/lvLC6Sjt8pETC3La8rGvhyYWSx0.jpg'),
        (34845, 'Lola Glaudini', '1971-11-24', 'From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia.

Lola Glaudini (born November 24, 1971, New York City, New York) is an American actress. She attended Bard College.

She was a regular on the CBS series Criminal Minds as Elle Greenaway, but left the show early in the second season because she reportedly became unhappy living in Los Angeles and wanted to return to the East Coast.

She had a recurring role on the HBO series The Sopranos as Federal Agent Deborah Ciccerone-Waldrup. Before those roles she appeared on NYPD Blue as Dolores Mayo, a heroin-addicted office assistant. She has guest starred in The Good Guys, The King of Queens, Andy Richter Controls the Universe, Boomtown, Special Unit 2, Law and Order: Criminal Intent, Las Vegas, Two And A Half Men, Monk, and ER. Lola also appeared briefly in the Neil LaBute film, Your Friends &amp; Neighbors.

In the 2006 film Invincible, she had a brief role as the first wife of Vince Papale, played by Mark Wahlberg, where she is seen berating Papale''s career failures and informs him of divorce.

She most recently played the role of Kat Damatto on the NBC mini-series Persons Unknown.', 'New York City - New York - USA', 1, '/xgp8VtX9rhsRot3fshmomStvg6b.jpg'),
